The paper discusses deep neural networks for compressing images and solving inverse problems, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses the use of underparameterization to prevent overfitting, which is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a simple architecture for the deep decoder, which may be of interest to researchers in multimedia (cs.MM) who are interested in efficient image and video compression.
